column1: #: description: Inclusive J/$\psi$ nuclear modification factor $R_{\rm AA}$ at midrapidity for $p_{\rm T} > 0.15$ GeV as a function of mean number of participating nucleons in Pb$-$Pb collisions at $\sqrt{s_{\rm NN}} = 5.02$ TeV. The low-$p_{\rm T}$ interval is removed to reject J/$\psi$ from photo-production. The correlated systematic uncertainty due to the pp reference cross section is not listed and amounts to 6.9%
column2: shown as the red box around unity in the paper figure.
